inn1.comm: a little bit of swing in to Watson, who leaves it outside off
right on target now, and Watson gets forward to defend
again Watson goes with the straight bat, watchfully, as Shahzad angles in to off stump
some swing away from the batsman now, and it's left to go through to Matt Prior
banged in short of a length and it's moving in to Watson, who leaves it alone
fuller and straighter, Watson drives clunkily to mid-on and can't find the gap
the first run is on the board, and it's a leg-bye off the thigh away behind square as Tremlett bowls a little too straight
better line now and Watson drives, uppishly as this ball doesn't come on as quick as he expected, and it's collected at mid-on
Watson tries to guide this one down past the two slips, but it's collected on the bounce at second slip
banged in short of a length, Watson pushes to point, he's being extra cautious out there
Watson gets off the mark now with a single, just guided into the ground and behind point
oh, you could have driven a small car through that gap between bat and pad, as Haddin drives waftily and Tremlett nips the ball back in through the gate - Haddin's lucky to survive that
there's the first boundary of the day, but it wasn't exactly off the middle as Watson drove uppishly just wide of mid-off, it evaded the fielder and ran away safely
left alone as this one nips back in and sails over the stumps

bouncer and Watson swings wildy! He's tried to pull that, with so much effort that he's lucky not to have thrown his back out. In any case, the ball bounced more than he expected and sailed through to Prior
jags back in off the seam and Watson gets an inside edge on to the pads
Shahzad is getting good bounce here, and this one is cut by Watson close to his body, into the ground and straight to point

gone! Shahzad deserved that wicket, he'd been getting them nip back off the seam and this one does the same, Watson tries to open the face and run it to third man but only succeeds in playing on to his off stump
Haddin faces his third ball and works a single off his hips to square leg
wide of off and swinging away, Clarke leaves it alone
straighter now and Clarke pushes defensively to cover
good line right on off stump and straightening, Clarke gets it away to point
Clarke gets across and punches to the off side, doesn't quite time it
and Clarke is off the mark with a hurried single as he pushes just wide of mid on
defended edgily back down the pitch
good bounce and carry through to Prior as it's left alone outside off
nipping back in again and it's short of a length, Clarke thrusts the bat forward and gets a single off the inside edge away through square leg
bouncer and Prior does well to take that one. That was above head height, I think Shahzad is lucky that wasn't called a wide
wider of off now and Haddin opens the face to guide this one through gully, and third man runs around to do the fielding
Haddin's had enough of being careful, he backs away and tries to drive down through cover but just finds mid off
that's a wonderful delivery from Tremlett, it angles back in and then moves away off the seam, thoroughly beating the straight bat of Clarke
good running now as Clarke gets one through square leg and puts the pressure on the fielder to get back for two
straight-bat defence this time from Clarke
pushed away off the back foot to cover
short of a length again, and it's pushed away to midwicket
again it's a good ball probing outside off, and it's pushed to cover
Haddin works this one with the angle through midwicket, just finds the gap nicely
Shahzad gets another one! Again he nips the ball back in, and Haddin drives at it, gets a thin edge back in on to his stumps and the seam movement has now done for both openers
fullish ball and White keeps it out
pushed back down past the bowler to mid-on
probing outside off, White gets across with a big stride and defends
bouncer! And it's quick, straight, and probably just a touch too high to really threaten White, who goes for the hook but can't connect
left alone outside off
straighter line now and Clarke nudges a single wide of mid-on
White pushes this one to off, good consistent lines from Tremlett

yeee-ouch! Tremlett uses his height to bang this one in short and White tries to defend, but cops it on the right hand, yanking it off the bat and takes the glove off immediately. The physio comes out to have a look. And for some reason Kevin Pietersen is supervising, patting White on the shoulder.
pushed out to the off side and can't find the gap
on the back foot, White defends
pushed away to the off side
well played by Clarke, he's used his feet here to walk down the pitch and across outside off, and lifts this ball over wide midwicket, safely and timed well enough to reach the boundary
slower ball now and it's left alone outside off
punched off the back foot wide of cover and Clarke finds a single
White hangs the bat out at this one and defends to cover
and this one is left alone
good line to start with, right on off stump, and it's defended
pulled away to midwicket but can't find the gap

ooooh dear! Clarke has not capitalised on his start. He's chased a wide one, which was there to be hit, but he's cut it straight to Bell who is just forward of point, what a disappointing end for the stand-in captain
pushed away defensively to off
good ball swinging back in and Hussey doesn't get the bat on that, takes it on the pad
defended to the off side again
bad ball, way down leg side and there's no doubt that's a wide
driven just wide of mid-off to get a single
thickish inside edge gets Hussey off the mark through square leg and that's his first ODI run since August 2009
yorker but it's not on line, and White pushes to point
there's an appeal now as White pushes outside off and the ball is taken by Prior, but Tony Hill isn't interested and it didn't look like an edge at first view - replays confirm bat hit pad
White throws the bat now as he gets a wider and fuller one, getting it uppishly to third man and it's collected inside the boundary
oh good shot! Short and wide, as was the ball that did for Clarke, but David Hussey cuts deliberately high over point and bounces that one safely away to the boundary
angled in to White, who pushes to the leg side
nudged away to point and White thinks of a single until Hussey roars a 'nooooo!'
defended back down the pitch
driven off the back foot and White didn't quite control that, edging it through the vacant gully region and way to third man
that's a pull that you'd probably short-arm jab, as Hussey just slaps it through midwicket but doesn't quite time it
another run for Hussey, who clips it off his pads through square leg
left alone outside off
well wide of off and Hussey leaves it
And another bites the dust! Tremlett probes outside off and gets one to seam away a touch, Hussey pushes off the back foot but straight to Strauss at gully, and he takes a good catch
Marsh gets off the mark with a flick off his pads through square leg
White watches this one through to Prior as it moves away off the seam
nudged towards the leg side
a stifled lbw shout here but that was clearly pitching a long way outside leg
fullish and straight, and Marsh pushes back to the bowler
clipped away through midwicket as Bresnan again bowls a touch too straight
bouncer, and White ducks under it - that's another one that is lucky not to have been called a wide
pushed to short cover and can't beat the field
oooh, White slashes at one wide of off and tries to cut hard, but it bounces more than expected and is taken by Prior
fullish and swinging back down the line, Marsh defends
on the hips, Marsh works it behind square and Matt Prior bolts across to do the fielding and ensures that is only a single
clunked away to mid-off

oh, here's a chance, White pulls and top edges high - high - high - and out to square leg, Prior races across and tries to make the ground, hurls himself at the last moment but falls a few inches short of getting his gloves on it. Perhaps he could have left that for fine leg or midwicket running around, but it was a good effort nonetheless
defended back down the pitch
defended away safely by Marsh
nudged away off the pads through square leg
Marsh cuts into the ground and straight to point
on the pads and Marsh defends
cuts this one fine, getting it away to third man to pick up two runs
England continue to target Marsh's pads and body - he pulls this one into the ground and behind square
pushed back down the pitch defensively
right, no coverage for that delivery so I can't tell you what happened
Tremlett pings another down from 12 ft, hitting back of a length and White finds an inside edge that squirts down to midwicket
England trying to tuck Marsh up, giving him no room outside off and this is defended back to the bowler
Tremlett goes too far on the tuck-him-up approach and slides this down the leg side
back on a length and line now, rewarded with a very correct defence from Marsh and "that's it!" from Prior
this is outside off stump but Marsh lets it go by for Australia's 71st dot ball
dot ball to finish another good over. Good effort from Tremlett to respond from World Cup disappointment with a spell like this
Bresnan has been fuller than Tremlett, suits him better and he lands this around off stump on a length, White eases forward to block
ripper! Pitches on a length and skids away, White's feet are rooted and it climbs past the outside edge
good running earns a couple here, White glancing towards deep square and sprinting hard to come back for the second
a misfield! Don't see many from England. Bell is the villain, diving over the ball at short cover to gift a single
banged in very short, Marsh thinks about a hook before deciding against it. The ball swerves late on Prior who has to dive to collect well
Bresnan reverts to a fuller length, angling into the hips and Marsh shoves it into the leg side
worked away for another single towards square leg
starts with a gentle, wobbling medium-pacer aiming for around off stump. White defends rather respectfully
no more respect from White! He aims an almighty drive down-town, as Australians like to say, didn't get much of it and it went very high, Tremlett hared after it but couldn't quite catch up
this time it's back to careful defence

White aims a mow. Horrid shot really, flat-footed swipe. He momentarily dragged his foot out before grounding it back in the crease. Prior had the bails off to all sorts of excitement but the third umpire confirmed White was home
finally White gets hold of one. I don't think he can stomach the prospect of Trott trundling in and bowling dot balls so aims a well-timed lofted drive well over mid-on for four
satisfied with his boundary White is happy to nudge this into the leg side. He might have combusted if he didn't get one away off Trott
starts accurately, no great turn or bite, but straight and defended
Marsh edges down the wicket and blocks towards Pietersen, who fumbled at point
neatly swept away behind square for a couple
lovely shot, minimal effort just good footwork to get to the pitch and chip into the straight midwicket region for four
now eased down the ground for a single and the game suddenly seems so much easier for the batsmen
good finish to the over for Tredwell, rolling it down on a sensible length and line and it's patted back to him. Sensible seems the word for Tredwell
"Aw!" screams Prior, who must be watching a different game. Marsh clipped this neatly to deep square
White's bat is looking a touch broader now and he full-faces this down the ground
a hint of width means Marsh can open the face and run this down to third man
Trott finds a straight line and good length. White steps forward to defend
more good lengths and lines from Trott. White picks out Strauss with a leg-side nudge
White has seen enough so aims a drive here, timing it not quite perfectly but well enough to pick a single down to long-on
hint of spin here as Tredwell rolls it down on a length, it unnerves White a touch in defence
more secure for White this time, easing down to long-on
good line and length from Tredwell, nothing more or less than that and Marsh blocks
fuller and Marsh squeezed out a well-timed sweep for a single
Tredwell holds this back a touch and White has plenty of time to aim a cut, too much time in fact and he mistimes it
ooh, looked a good shout as White misses an attempted sweep. Probably hit outside the line. England opted not to review
worked away into space for a single
full-faced chip-drive from White, clearing the infield to take a couple
touch leg-sided from Trott allows White to lean this into the midwicket region. Steady flow of runs since the quicks left the attack
Marsh drops this to cover, jogs a single. Simple when you know how
Trott is rewarded for a good length and line, cutting his fingers across the ball, with a forward block
soft hands is not something you think of when talking about White but this was rather delicately placed behind square on the leg side for a strike-stealing single
patted back to Tredwell
aimed wide of off but White was on the move, heading even further outside off to hammer a sweep fine of deep square for four
White gets deep into his crease to punch a drive wide of extra cover for one
Marsh gets a single with a well-timed cut, with help from point who dived over the ball
another delicate touch from White, uses the slightest hint of width to run a back-cut to third man. Fancy shot for one
fifty stand! Good one, too. Marsh pushes this towards point, steals the single. No fuss at all just careful batting
hint of air here actually, fullish length, Marsh works it into the leg side
starts a touch too short to the right hander and White picks out point with a cut. Trott threw it back poorly to Prior who couldn't take it and allowed an overthrow
this time it's worked back to the bowler
Marsh aims a booming sweep but can't get hold of it and finds short fine leg
classic Yardy. Not a category to fill DVD shops, but still, angled in and cramping Marsh for room on the cut
this time Marsh earns a single, picking this off into space

big shot from Marsh brings a big shout from Prior! Marsh edged down the wicket to drive expansively, some spin took it past the outside edge and Prior had the bails off in a flash. Marsh though, was equally swift in getting his back foot back and it looks very tight. Marsh gets the benefit of the doubt
after all that fuss this is driven firmly back down the ground for one
touch too short from Tredwell but it's sticking in the pitch and White has to heave his cut shot, means the timing isn't ideal so it's just a single to deep point
Marsh picks a gap at cover with the softest of hands. These two looking in good order now
big gap either side of Bell at short midwicket but White's leg-side nurdle finds the man
hint of turn and extra bounce keeps White careful as he works this to Bell again at short midwicket
Yardy darts this in full and straight and Marsh can't get the single he wants
this time it is worked wide of midwicket for a jogged single
White looking to give himself room, Yardy doesn't let him so it's worked to leg for one
another single as Marsh sweeps powerfully
again White wants room to bang over cover, but Yardy is following him, taking pace off the ball and White has to force a back-foot drive to cover
same set up as last delivery really, intriguing little battle, White this time gets a single down to long-off with his back-foot drive
White gets deep into his crease to really heave a cut shot, all for a single to deep point
Tredwell holds this back a touch and Marsh has to wait and wait before turning to leg
this time he gets a single, picking off into space
White pushes down the ground, no fuss, but a very safe single
ah, lovely shot. Marsh got all of this. Down on one knee and sweeping very hard into a gap wide of deep square
follows up the boundary with a strike-stealing single. Good work from Marsh he's looked a notch above all the other Australian batsmen today
another excellent Marsh boundary. Gets deep into his crease and outside leg to time a cut shot wonderfully to the point boundary
nothing on offer here as Yardy gets his line tighter to off
fired in on a length and line and patted to midwicket
Marsh earns a single this time pushing down the ground
White trades another single, gently patted to long-on
fraction short from Yardy and Marsh has all of it! Gets back, picks the gap he wants wide of long-on and smashes a  pull shot straight into that area. Really good stuff from Marsh
White does the sensible thing and pats a single into space to bring Marsh back on strike
Marsh down the wicket but blocks back to the bowler
Marsh wants a single at least every ball and he happily pushes this down the ground for one
White repeats the dose, driving carefully down to long-on
Tredwell tosses this up a fraction and is rewarded with a respectful block
even the edges working for Marsh now. This squirts off the outside edge down past short third man for three
full-faced guide past the bowler
flick of the wrists earns White a single towards square leg
fuller and quicker from Yardy, Marsh jabs a defence down on time
ooh, Marsh aims a nothing sort of dab cut that almost cannons onto the stumps, bounces over, hits Prior's gloves and bobbles onto the stumps. Creating all kinds of confusion
tossed up this time and defended
carefully angled away square on the off side
starts very well, bang on target. Marsh has to hurry forward into a defence
good energy from Shahzad already, finding extra bounce from a length that jars the splice as Marsh defends
well played here, Marsh uses the fraction of width to angle this to third man
straight onto the ideal off-stump line to the right-hander this time. White securely behind it to defend
too much width allows White to free his arms with a back-foot drive, only earns a single but he's a good wingman for Marsh at the moment
oops, Shahzad gets his line wrong, slipping down the leg side
and again! The crowd love it, which is a sign of the times. Shoved down the leg side again
fifty for Marsh! Now the crowd have something to cheer about. Gets there in style too, clipping off his legs for a couple. Crucial fifty that off 64 deliveries
slow and loopy from Yardy, which is rare. Marsh defends carefully
White lines up a reverse-sweep, Yardy responds by shoving it too far down the leg side
blocked carefully off the back foot to cover
White edges down the wicket, lining up a booming drive before deciding on a more careful pat
Marsh down the wicket now, picking off a single to long-on
ah this is a wonderful, wonderful shot. Easing down the track and rather than smack it, White picked out a gap wide of long-off and timed it away for four

Yardy strikes, soft dismissal that. Held back and tossed up from the bowler, White was a touch early on a drive but rather than go through with the shot he checked it, chipped it back wide of Yardy who dived smartly to his left  to take the catch. England really needed that
this hurries Marsh in defence here, thudding into the pads
eep, all the England supporters gasp as Tremlett dives to field smartly on the fine-leg boundary. Not a natural but good work to save a boundary as Marsh clipped off his pads
Shahzad around the wicket and finds an inside edge that bobbles off the body and Smith calls through a swift single
ooh, Smith plays back to a full ball, gets into a strange position but defends well
another drag-on! Smith departs. Awful shot. Feet stuck in place and aiming a booming drive well wide of off, comes off the inside edge and cannons onto the stumps
starts with a thick outside edge that goes well wide of the newly-installed slip
Hauritz has to stay with Marsh here and starts well enough by defending back to the bowler
worked back to the bowler again
this time Yardy gets a single, picking off into space on the leg side
Marsh stands tall to pat a defence towards midwicket
Marsh down the wicket and drives sweetly but Pietersen scoots round to field well at long-off
neatly defended back to the bowler
Marsh defends back down the pitch
flicked away off the pads

and Australia's downward spiral continues. Hauritz has just tried to flick this uppishly over square leg but gets it too high and Trott running around from fine leg has time to make his ground and slides to take a very good catch, nearly face-planting in the process
on the pads, can't quite get it away
short and wide, Marsh cuts hard and forward of point, that's a very good shot but Pietersen in the deep runs around to make a terrific save on the boundary
defended back down the pitch
Lee on the back foot defends back towards Yardy
worked away to midwicket
down leg side and Lee pulls, but there's a short fine leg who saves the single
Lee leans forward to defend

gone! Yardy strikes, and this one simply moves on with the arm, a bit quicker and Lee plays all around it, trying to guide it through the slips. The ball crashes into off stump, and Australia crash towards an extremely disappointing total.
there's a confident lbw shout immediately, but it's turned down by Tony Hill and Strauss decides against a review
on the hips, but Marsh can't get it away
full and straight, Marsh clips it to long-on and can't get back for a second, so Dougie has to face up now
Bollinger's off the mark, he clunks one into the ground and it drops at his feet, Marsh calls him through for a quick single
slower ball, good variation as it wasn't that much slower at 124kph, and Marsh could only bunt back down the pitch
on the pads again, Marsh clips it through midwicket for a single
almost yorker length now and Bollinger does really well to push that back past the bowler, and hits it well enough to get back for two, to ensure Marsh has the strike
wide down leg side to start with, and Marsh lets it through to Prior
pushed back down the pitch
aaah, another wide down leg side, Shahzad hasn't got his line right in this over
better line now as it's full and straight, Marsh gets an inside edge onto the pad and it runs along the ground to Prior

ooh, Shahzad has dropped a tough return chance! Marsh drove it hard back at the bowler, who thrust his right hand out and couldn't hold on - not an easy one by any means but had that stuck it would have been massive trouble for Australia
Marsh cuts hard to point and they come through for a hesitant single, Morgan's throw at the bowler's end isn't accurate enough
pushed to the off side
thwacked into the pitch and back at the bowler! Dougie gets it off the middle, but Shahzad deflects the ball to mid-off and prevents a run
swinging down the leg side, Marsh clips it fine but it's picked up by Shahzad at fine leg
oh, Dougie, what are you doing? He's pushed it straight to gully and taken off for a run, sensibly sent back by Marsh, and the throw from gully missed but Bollinger was in trouble had it hit
beats the bat now, as he tries to force it through cover
pushed out through wide mid-off for a single
again Tremlett aims at the pads of Marsh, who flicks through square leg
Bollinger throws everything at a pull and slaps it behind square, wide enough of fine leg that he can scurry back for a well-judged second run

and there's a boundary, we haven't seen many of them lately. It's swinging on to the pads, which has been a definite plan to Marsh, and he's flicked it through the gap at square leg along the ground, all the way to the boundary
drives down the ground this time, in the air and it bounces to long-on
hmm, Bollinger has got away with one here, he's pulled and got a top edge that lobs safely in the infield. Not smart from Bollinger, with ten overs still to bat
ah, four more runs now as Marsh just gets a bit of pad on this and it beats the diving Prior, and trickles away to the boundary
on the hips now and Marsh tickles it around the corner

full and straight, Bollinger drives to mid-on and takes off for a quick single, keeping the strike. And the throw from mid-on hits the stumps and allows an overthrow, so in fact Marsh will have the strike. But what's happened here? Tony Hill might have called over already, so the overthrow has been disallowed.
and an angry Dougie takes his frustration out with a powerful crunch through cover, finding the gap and finding the boundary!
flicked away through square leg
good, hard running from Marsh, who clips a couple behind square leg
oooh, a missed run-out chance here as Marsh cuts fine, and hesitates while taking the single, Trott's throw at the non-striker's end from point would have had Marsh out by miles, but it's missed
ooh, Bollinger tries the pull again and mistimes it again! It lobs up towards mid-on and lands safely
good drive back past the bowler from Marsh, who picks up two more
what a good shot from Bollinger! He's rocked back and cut that through cover, all the way along the ground to the boundary!
flicked away through midwicket to give Marsh the strike
angled in to the pads of Marsh, who clips through midwicket and gets two runs, Bollinger dives headlong into his ground at the non-striker's end to beat the throw
ah, there goes Marsh! He's advanced to Yardy and just lifted him with excellent timing over wide midwicket, and has cleared the boundary
turned away behind square leg
pushed away to midwicket and can't get the single
pushed away defensively to the off side
and one block is enough for Bollinger, who throws everything at a slap back past the bowler to get a single to long-on, and would you believe it, that's the 50 partnership
driven away through cover
oh, another ripper from Douglas Bollinger! He's quickly on to the back foot and makes Tredwell's ball look shorter than it was, crunching it through cover for another boundary!
and this time he defends with supreme concentration
and another single as Bollinger turns it to short fine leg
tossed up on middle stump and Bollinger jams a drive back down to long-on
quicker and flatter and Marsh has done really well to cut that fine and out of reach of the backward point, but the slide from the man in the deep keeps that to three
Bollinger advances and smashes it on the bounce to long on
oh yes! That's class from Marsh as he lifts Yardy over wide midwicket, and the most impressive thing about that is his placement, there's nobody in the deep there so it's a safe shot
another boundary and Marsh moves to 95! He's slog swept that one with power, just wide of the man in the deep and it bounces over the rope

Marsh brings up his century with a six! Oh, what a moment for Marsh! He's launched a big slog sweep high, really high and for a moment it seemed it was going to fall short, but the man at deep wide midwicket backed back and tripped over the rope as that ball landed safely a couple of metres over the boundary
punched back down towards mid off
Bollinger backs away and tries to slap it through cover, can't connect
nudged back past the bowler for a quick single, good, sensible stuff from Bollinger
good yorker from Bresnan, and Marsh keeps it out
full toss on the leg side, Marsh works it to square leg but can't get a run - a run-out chance is missed as Bollinger sent Marsh back
on the stumps now and Marsh pushes to cover to keep the strike
driven to cover, can't find the gap
smashed back at Tredwell, who does really well to field off his own bowling and prevent a run
another cover drive finds the fielder
pushed back down to mid on for a single
Bollinger goes the slog, but gets an inside edge to short fine leg
Marsh drives a full toss to long-on
goes for the slog but doesn't middle it
another boundary, Marsh is really hitting the ball well and finding the gaps - this one is flicked over square leg and bounces away to the rope
he's gone for the pull now but there's a man in the deep, who cuts that off

bouncer! Bollinger goes for the hook, but it's crashed into his helmet and run away to third man for a leg bye. He doesn't look in too much strife, he's just bending down to do up his shoelace. He's fine!
full and on leg side, clipped to square leg
pushed to point and the call is "noo, yessss", and yet another throw from England misses the stumps - they've had their chances, and Marsh might have been in trouble at the striker's end again there

aah, Dougie's wonderful innings comes to an end! He's slapped Tremlett back over his head and in the air, but running around from mid-off is Shahzad, who actually takes a really good catch running back with the flight
ah, well, that's a rather unexpected end, as Marsh flicks high in the air to deep midwicket and the catch is taken

inn2.comm: and a good start it is too, no wild pace or anything, just the humble merits of line and length. Strauss defends but tentatively
again Lee searches for the off-stump and finds Strauss defending very carefully. Placing the bat in line with the ball
the fuller length here draws Strauss into something vaguely more attacking but it finds mid-on
shorter from Lee, Strauss pulls straight to square leg
Strauss is away, England are away. Gets another good back-of-a-length delivery from Lee and nudges into the leg side
Lee aims full for Prior's first delivery and it's jabbed out to cover. Good start from Lee
oh! Starts very, very quickly indeed. Short ball which Strauss was waiting for but it was a bottom edge this far from the stumps. All of those hit for England, the luck is with them
this again is full of pace but the line wide of off allows Strauss to leave
big grunt as he delivers but this is too far down leg
and again. Big appeal from Haddin, but when isn't there?
better line this time, back of a length around off stump. Strauss is right behind it
the pace effect! It just gets a batsman's beans going. Wide of off and Strauss slashes wildly at fresh air
banged in short. Very short. Too short for the umpire's liking. This is turning into a long over
shortish this time but only gets up around hip level and Strauss wheels away a pull to fine leg
good finish to a lengthy over. Tait sliding the ball swiftly back into Prior who defends loosely
Lee hitting those infamous 'right areas' and Strauss can only defend
good areas from Lee, hugging off stump on a fullish length. Good stare too as he collects in his follow through
a very straight delivery finds an equally straight bat. Lee is looking in good order so far
wow, this is an excellent shot. Lee again hammering away on a good length and line, Strauss stood tall and punched a back-foot drive wide of mid-off

Prior's comeback is over! Lee is rewarded for a very good start. Good length ball around off stump, Prior got into position to defend but it clipped the outside edge and eased through to Watson at first slip
excellent finish to an excellent Lee over. First ball to Trott has him rushing to defend
ooh, Tait bangs in another short ball and really rushed Strauss on the pull. Got it high on the bat and it looped short of fine leg
another thunder-bolt short ball. Trott had only just thought about pulling and found the ball climbing towards his face. In the end he flapped a top edge that sailed over Haddin for four
Tait is grunting as loud as he's bowling quick. Very. Happily for Trott this is outside off stump so he leaves alone
extreme pace just seems to create drama. Even leg bye, thudding off the thigh into the leg side, seems thoroughly hectic
Strauss is sitting on the back foot waiting for something short. Tait lands a shortish ball, rather than a bouncer, and Strauss is in position to bang a pull shot to the midwicket fence

review. Well well well. It was slipped down the leg side, Strauss missed an attempted fiddle to leg. Clipped the hip but Haddin thought it was more and persuaded Clarke to gamble. Tait wasn't interested and rightly so

Lee is yet to bowl a bad ball. This is perfectly straight and Trott defends back to him. Lee is full of puppy-dog excitement, despite his advancing years, and flings the ball back at Trott after he collects
touch shorter this time and Trott stands tall in defence
neatly played, Trott walks across his stumps and flicks into the leg side
again Lee hammers it down on a length outside off stump. Trott hurries to defend

fuller ball, slower ball too. Cleverly aimed outside off to try and find the drag on. It was an inside edge, squirted to square leg, Strauss called one, Trott didn't go straight away and if the throw at the bowler's end hit, Trott would have gone
Strauss gets back and, with a little help from the inside edge, works this to square leg
banged in short, not a great start really, Strauss happily pulls to deep midwicket
another bouncer, but a sharper one this time. Trott gets into position to pull but it gets too high on him so he ducks out the shot
good follow-up ball. Pushed full and across the right hander. Trott aimed an airy drive but missed
back of a length and Trott whips behind square
Strauss didn't get hold of his pull shot here, probably a bit too quick on the shot. Collects a single for the effort
Trott shuffles across his stumps to defend back to the bowler. Bollinger collects and shapes to fire a throw back at Trott, who is too consumed with marking his guard to notice
lots of short balls to Strauss. Not sure why because he plays them well. This gets a touch high on him so he ducks out a pull shot
again this is a touch short. Strauss wanted, desperately, to cut but it bounced a touch on him
some width means Strauss gets to throw his arms at it, timed well enough but to extra cover
short, short, short. Strauss wheels a firm pull to jog a single to deep square
for the first time Lee offers Trott a hint of room and is duly punished. Trott timed this cover drive dreamily and without anyone expecting it, it flew to the ropes
having taken the boundary he can shoulder arms. And as Ravi Shastri could have said, 'when he leaves them, they stay left'
Bollinger persists with the short stuff and has Strauss in bother here as he misses an attempted pull shot. Crashed into the stomach
the product of all the short balls is Strauss hanging back so Bollinger's change-up fuller delivery has Strauss pinned to the crease in defence
this time Strauss is more steady in working to midwicket
Trott hops to drop this into the off side and calls Strauss through for one with a "yeah, come on"

Bollinger's good day just got much better! Strauss was again pinned on the crease and missed his attempted defence. Thudded into the pad and was given out. Strauss headed off but Trott has called a review! Height could be the issue.... but no, it is indeed hitting the top of leg stump
gone first ball! Pietersen departs and Bollinger is on fire! That dreaded inside edge again. Pushed across Pietersen who stood tall to defend, clipped the inside edge and cannoned onto the stumps
who starts tidily enough forcing Trott to defend
touch too short this time allows Trott to whip into the leg side
touch of swing here for Watson, just offering to wobble away. Bell careful in defence
touch of extra bounce for Watson has Bell standing tall to drop this into the off side and defend
good work from Watson, attacking the stumps. Bell eases into a defence
Bell glides a single to third man which means he's on strike for Douggie's hat-trick ball!
oooh! Almost! Banged in a short ball and Bell didn't get much of a pull shot it looped wide of fine leg
shoved short and wide across Bell, who thinks about cutting before deciding against it
this is left alone outside off stump
Bollinger has a packed offside field and is pushing the ball across Bell, who so far resists
back on a straighter line, Bell gets into line and defends comfortably
again Bell gets a sighter outside off stump. He watches carefully before lifting his arms and bat out of trouble
Doug sprints in, even quicker than he delivers, Bell leaves alone again outside off
Trott does what he enjoys most, shuffling across his stumps to flick to leg
this is left all alone outside off stump
a hint of inside edge means this squirts towards fine leg for a single
ooh, Bell beaten outside off. Just decked away a fraction and Bell aimed one of those horrible bat-far-from body glides to third man that caused him so much trouble earlier in his career
more solid this time, rocking forward to defend
Bell has seen enough and sets off on a jaunt down the wicket, Watson sees him coming and goes short and wide, Bell slashes out to deep cover. All in one ball
Bollinger wants to do it all! Short and Bell works a single to square leg and Bollinger hares off after it. No real need to but he's having a ball
back of a length from the bowler, forcing Trott to defend carefully
fuller length this time, good variation. Trott gets forward to defend to cover
slower ball, he runs in even quicker to confuse the batsman, Trott isn't bothered and defends
scream from the bowler as he delivers, again Trott gets fully behind a defence
this is a touch shorter and slower, Trott watches it carefully onto the bat steers it to third man
classic Trott, shuffles across his stumps and works a single to leg
Bell fancies a dart at Watson. Who wouldn't? But Watson's pace, line and length is too good
plenty of oohs and aah from the Australian fielders as Bell drove this sweetly, but airily down the ground for four. Lee flew from mid-on to try an intercept, but couldn't reach it
this time Bell defends
inside edge again! How many have we seen today!? Plenty, that's how many. This slides off an that edge just past the stumps and runs away to fine leg
Trott is solidly forward to defend. Another eventful over
short ball to start with, plenty quick too. Bell though always seems to have time on his side and eases back to defend
top shot this time. Bell stands up on his toes and punches a drive through cover
fired up fuller here, wide of off too. Bell leaves alone. It was, however, a no ball so free hit
as usual the free hit is an exercise in anti-climax. Bell gives himself room to slug a bouncer but misses
enough width here for Bell to steer down to third man
good length from Tait, full and offering to swing in. Trott blocks
again this is a touch wide, Trott guides to deep cover and ambles a single
worked off the pads to midwicket, straight to the fielder
good lines and lengths from Watson, Trott carefully drives to point
hint of a slower ball has Trott driving uneasily back to the bowler
Trott emulates the man bowling to him and pings a drive to mid-on
again Trott picks out mid-on. Good pressure building by Watson
enough width here for Trott to unfurl a well-timed cover drive. The sweeper scoots round to field on the boundary
pushed away to the off side
left alone outside off and it thumps the gloves of Haddin
again it's left alone
no shot offered once again, as Tait probes outside off
cut hard as Bell gets some more width from Tait, and Watson on the boundary keeps it to one
left alone outside off
tossed up as Bell uses his feet, and then defends
turns in from outside off, Bell cuts through point
wristy work from Trott, as he takes one from well outside off and flicks it through mid-on
beaten outside off as Hauritz gets some drift away from the batsman, who is drawn into a drive and can't connect
reverse sweep this time from Trott, and White does the chasing down to third man
flicked away towards square leg
Tait probes just outside off and, like the celery sticks at a kid's birthday party, that has been left untouched
pushed back down the pitch towards Tait
on the hips of Bell, who turns it around the corner and picks up a couple
good attacking line right on off stump, it's nudged away to the off side
nips it back in off the pitch, but another one is allowed to go through to Haddin
banged in a bit short of a length, and a single is worked through midwicket
Bell goes for the reverse sweep again, but it's been reverse successful. Didn't get anything on it.
nudged back down the pitch
Hauritz turns it in to Bell, who flicks through square
more drift from Hauritz, and a tiny bit of spin, and in the end Trott decided not to play
cut away off the back foot
dead-batted back down the pitch
Trott walks across his stumps and flicks this through square leg
nudged to the off side but can't find a gap
Bell waits on this one and pushes to off, again happy to defend
Bell just opens the face and glides this one through the vacant cordon and down to third man
pushed back down the pitch
this time it's Trott who guides one to third man for a comfortable single
good ball, a touch quicker and on line, it's defended
pushed away defensively again
tossed up way outside off, and Trott forces it through mid-on, refusing to be told where he should hit the ball

turned through square leg and the man in the deep keeps that to one, though Trott wanted two, was turned back and made an ungainly dive, getting his glove in the crease though the bat was raised. The third umpire is called, but Trott is safe.
clipped away through mid-on again, easy as you like for Trott
Bell uses his feet and defends
bouncer from Bollinger, and Trott isn't interested
clipped away through midwicket but can't find a run
clipped off the pads behind square leg
defended away safely by Bell
good ball angles across Bell, who plays and misses
Bell gets a little impatient and advances, but can't get it away
beaten outside off, as this one goes on straight and drifts away a touch
tossed up outside off, and Trott drives down towards long off
turned away towards square leg
Trott looks to cut this one but can't connect as it stays a little low, Haddin whips the bails off, for practice
fuller and straighter, Trott flicks through midwicket
pushed down towards mid on
pushed back to the bowler, shouts of catch it but that bounced well short

oh, Smith has struck second ball! And that was a pretty poor shot from Trott, who has pulled in the air straight to the catching man at short midwicket. He's picked the fielder out precisely. It may have been the topspinner, bounced a touch more than Trott expected.
tossed up on line, and Morgan defends
cut away through point
Bell just nudges this one through the gap at cover
Morgan defends, and that's a very good over from Smith first up
Bell turns this one through the leg side to get another single
Hauritz comes around the wicket to Morgan, who pushes to the off side
a flatter ball from Hauritz now and Morgan lap sweeps that around to fine leg
driven down towards long-on
and this one slides down the leg side, Haddin whips the bails off at the second attempt but there was no chance of Morgan being out of his ground
punched away through point
this one is tossed up and drops a bit on Morgan, who pushes to the off side
pushed away towards point
angles this one across Morgan, who defends
Morgan tries to cut but this ball is too full and slides on, he crunches it into the turf
driven away to long off to keep the scoreboard ticking over, slowly
Bell does the same now, drives a single to long off
defended by Morgan
another one slides down leg and Tony Hill has called that a wide
tossed up outside off and it doesn't spin much, Bell defends
Bell pulls to Hussey at midwicket, can't get it through the field
a flicky drive to long-on, the singles keep ticking over
oh, Morgan has paddle-swept this and only just got bat on ball, getting it so fine that he's picked up a couple
defended back down the pitch
Morgan advances, and then defends
Bell watches the first one carefully and leaves outside off
gone! Lee strikes second ball of his spell, just as Smith did, and indeed it's Smith who takes the catch at backward point as Bell tries to use the pace and force a cut through the field.
Yardy pushes this one back down the pitch to an enthusiastic Brett Lee
fuller and straighter, Yardy defends
"Nooooo!" comes the loud shout from Yardy, as he pushes it to cover
Yardy gets off the mark, guiding one through point
Hauritz is around the wicket to both left-handers, and Yardy chops a paddle sweep around the corner
well flighted and angling in to Morgan, who pushes to off
Morgan advances, Hauritz goes for the quicker one and the batsman can't get it through midwicket
goes for the sweep now and lobs off the pad flap, Haddin sees it go over his head but loses the ball, and hopes he hasn't missed a chance - leg byes were called so he was fine
pushed away through the off side
driven down towards long off
quick and straight, it's defended
on the pads and it just rolls out to the leg side, they scamper a leg bye and a sliding Lee can't pick up and throw in one movement
full and straight, it's pushed for a single wide of midwicket
cut hard into the ground and it's collected at point
really good quick running as Yardy nudges to the off side and hares off immediately
wide of off and Morgan tries to cut, can't connect, and that has been called a wide by Paul Reiffel
banged in at the hips and Morgan works a single to midwicket
tossed up from around the wicket, and it's driven to long-off
punched to cover and Yardy can't find the gap
ah, well played by Yardy as he advanced and opens up to loft Hauritz over cover, and Marsh in the deep can't save it with an ungainly dive
defended away to the off side
goes for the paddle sweep now
ah, now Morgan goes for the pull and gets it all the way over the boundary, powerful shot!

pushed away through the leg side and Hauritz is in trouble, he seems to have hurt his right shoulder sliding to save that boundary. Immediately it's obvious that this is a serious injury, he is down and in pain, lying on his back and the physio comes out to help him. Really nasty to see that sort of injury, he just sort of jarred the shoulder during the slide.

He's walking off the field now and is in serious pain. You'd have to think he's in doubt for the World Cup now, which brings Xavier Doherty back into consideration. What a rotten piece of luck for Hauritz, who was just making his way back after a summer of being harshly treated by the selectors.
defended back down the pitch
good shot, as it's cut away behind point and wide enough of third man to reach the boundary
defended with the full face of the bat
pushed through the gap at cover
a slower bouncer to end the over, and it's pulled to deep midwicket
decent start from Watto, back of a length around off stump, angled towards point
touch of extra bounce here surprises Yardy, who stares down at the pitch suspiciously
now a firm drive picks out mid-off
play and a miss outside off. Watson creaks up and delivers this invitingly outside off but Yardy's swish finds nothing
beaten again! Slower ball just outside off stump. Yardy dabbles at it half-heartedly and fails to connect
precious bat on ball earns Yardy a single to cover. It also steals him the strike
starts short and Yardy does the right thing by working it square of the wicket on the leg side for one to bring Morgan on strike
good line from Bollinger, hugging off stump and Morgan stands tall to drop to cover and speed through for a single
Yardy works a single, opening the face to steer to third man
neatly done from Morgan. Picking off riskless singles. This is short and he pushes gently down the ground
oops, Bollinger aims a yorker but it's way too full, and wide down leg and it slips away past a diving Haddin for five wides
back on the right line here, the length is good too and Yardy gets fully behind it
Yardy pinches the strike again by dropping this past the bowler and scampering through
good start from Watson, full and straight and Yard's drive finds cover
full again and Yardy's drive is mistimed and bobbles to cover
banged in shorter and Yardy edged down the wicket before heaving this up in the air towards deep square, luckily for him the poor timing meant it went on the bounce
this is more secure, steered wide of point
Morgan dances down the wicket and drives firmly into the ground back to Watson. Crowd catch

that could be the match! Watson gets the key wicket and Tait, of all people, holds on to a good catch. Morgan tried to flick it to the midwicket boundary it went high and Tait had to run back from mid-on and steady himself to take a tough chance
Bresnan nudges his first ball into the leg side
Lee finds a good length and line, nothing for Bresnan to work with and it's blocked
this time it's worked past point for a single
Yardy drops this by his toes and calls Prior through for the single
Bresnan clunks a firm drive straight to extra cover
Bresnan gets a touch of width and throws his big arms through the ball sending it to third man
Bresnan again heaves at the ball, clearing the infield without much timing but it earns him a couple
this time it's securely blocked to cover
Yardy lines up a leg-side thwack but Watson sees what's happening and throws it outside off, Yardy ends up steering a single wide of cover

Watson's the man! The runner has caused all kinds of trouble.  Bresnan dropped this by his toes, and Yardy set off for one a non-existent single, Prior sent him back but Watson had gathered and threw down the stumps at the bowler's end. Crazy single attempted
this is similar to last time round but the single is completed without fuss
Tredwell watches his first ball carefully and allows it to pass by outside off
short ball dug in from Lee, Bresnan heaves a pull shot without timing it. Trickles down to deep midwicket
Tredwell is away, very carefully flicking a single to leg
carefully blocked into the infield
short ball, slower too, and Bresnan saw all of it. Stood back, cleared the front leg and slapped it to the midwicket rope
full ball wide of off, Bresnan gave himself room and in the end left it alone
poor delivery, with fine leg up a short ball angled into the leg side is a bad idea. Bresnan helps it on its way past the short fine leg
Watson constantly finding a good area and Tredwell can only pat back to the bowler
nicely-timed drive here, Tredwell thought it was through but a diving stop at cover saved
touch shorter from Watson and Tredwell steers to third man
flicks the pad and they get through for a leg bye
defended back down the pitch
and he guides a single to third man to finish the over
jams the bat down to defend
bouncer now and he ducks under it
again they scamper through for a leg bye as he can't get it away off the bat
Bresnan uses the pace of Tait, as he cuts in the air, it bounces down to third man
and a roar from Tait as he sends this one down, Tredwell cuts behind square
clunked into the turf and Bresnan can't get it away
Watson lands a perfect yorker that Tredwell just about stabs out in time
an inside edge almost squeezes though bat an pad but it drops by Tredwell's feet and Bresnan is on him for a single
Bresnan is not moving his feet much, he's standing and for the moment delivering a single, thumped to long-on
poor delivery and it's just what England needed. Tredwell gets space to free his arms outside off and clunks it away for four
fuller and straighter this time and Tredwell blocks back to the bowler. Really needs singles off balls like that
driven firmly, if not with the best timing, back down the ground to steal the strike
starts well, up and around off stump, Tredwell confidently forward to block a single to point
another flat-footed swish from Bresnan, he's been connecting fairly well so far but this is bottom-edged and Haddin collects
repeats the shot and this time toe-ends to mid-off
cracker! Bollinger is all over this match! Jags one away with the angle and it skims past the edge
beaten again! Slower ball this time, turning into a very very good over
excellent over ends with Bresnan hopping to defend back to the bowler
Tredwell leans forward and drops a single to cover
Bresnan gets his pad in the way of one which would have been a wide down the leg side. Bobbles off the pads for a leg bye
good lines and lengths from Hussey and it's nudged into the leg side
this time Tredwell gets the single, pushing into space
Bresnan gets down on one knee and heaves to long-on who scoots round to field very smartly
nothing on offer here, excellent over from Hussey
Yardy stands tall to drop this by his toes. Prior scampers through for a single
Bollinger has his third! Short ball that Bresnan tried to flip up to the third man boundary, couldn't get it fine enough and Watson ran in to take the catch
worked square of the wicket where a good diving stop earns a massive cheer. Australia buzzing!
Tredwell clipped this into the leg side, there shouldn't have been two but he ran sharply to come back for it
It's Bollinger's day! Tredwell is late coming forward and it smacks him flush on the pad in front. One more to go!
Bollinger looking for his fifth wicket, attacks off stump but finds Tremlett defending to point
Shahzad aims a wristy drive to point
clipped to leg, Shahzad jogs through for one
oops, Hussey gets his line wrong here shoving it down the leg side
driven without much power into the covers
Shahzad opens the face to steer a single
pushed back to the bowler, Shahzad wants Tremlett to take one but there is nothing there
that's it! Clarke has finished it off! Tremlett clipped to midwicket, Shahzad set off for one that was never there and couldn't turn back in time. Australia have a hat-trick of wins!
